      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CRUISING NAT (4) flew the lids with a fast early split and led until late but gathered in when a 1.5 lengths second at this track over 390m in 22.54. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Leading chance again. LILLY'S WISH (8) has been hard to follow lately, running fourth (23.12) last time but prior to that ran very well when placed at Geelong. Well placed here and can atone this time. PAW LARA (5) has an excellent record here having never missed the placings in three starts, including two wins. Missed the frame latest (24.76) when sixth over 425m at Bendigo in a Bottom Up - Grade 6. Looks one of the chances. SNAPPER HEAD (1) is worth consideration.",
